        "content": [
          "Some French words hid. Others didn't",
          "bother. Tier 5 meets both.",
          "",
          "The hidden ones wore English clothes",
          "for so long that nobody remembers:",
          "",
          "  curfew    — couvre-feu (cover the fire)",
          "  pedigree  — pied de grue (crane's foot)",
          "  mortgage  — dead pledge",
          "  vinegar   — sour wine",
          "",
          "The unhidden ones never even tried:",
          "chef, fiancé, genre, debris, ballet,",
          "coup d'état, hors d'oeuvre, déjà vu.",
          "",
          "English absorbs what it needs and",
          "leaves the rest in plain sight. Both",
          "are Norman legacy. Both are yours now."
